@page "/render-foreach"
<PageTitle>Render &amp; Foreach - Saascade Docs</PageTitle>

<h1>Render &amp; Foreach</h1>

<main class="documentation">

    <section class="card">

        <h2>Render</h2>

        <p class="subtitle">
            The <code>&lt;Render&gt;</code> component is a utility for conditionally
            rendering content without introducing extra DOM elements.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <pre><code>&lt;Render&gt;
    @@ChildContent
&lt;/Render&gt;</code></pre>

    </section>

    <section class="card">

        <h2>Foreach</h2>

        <p class="subtitle">
            The <code>&lt;Foreach&gt;</code> component iterates over a collection
            and renders a template for each item — a declarative alternative to
            <code>@@foreach</code> in Razor markup.
        </p>

        <pre><code>&lt;Foreach Items="items" Context="item"&gt;
    &lt;Li&gt;@@item.Name&lt;/Li&gt;
&lt;/Foreach&gt;</code></pre>

    </section>

    <section class="card">

        <h2>ListOf</h2>

        <p class="subtitle">
            The <code>&lt;ListOf&gt;</code> component renders a typed list of items,
            combining iteration with list-specific rendering logic.
        </p>

        <pre><code>&lt;ListOf Items="products" Context="product"&gt;
    &lt;Card&gt;
        &lt;CardTitle&gt;@@product.Name&lt;/CardTitle&gt;
    &lt;/Card&gt;
&lt;/ListOf&gt;</code></pre>

    </section>

</main>
